values: Well I haven't updated in a while and I'm in a pretty good mood right now so I thought I would.  Hmm..what is going on.. well tomorrow is mine and Justin's 6 month anniversary and that is pretty exciting.  It has been a wonderful 6 months and totally worth it..  Today I have to work on a project for Spanish about Costa Rica.  I am going to make a poster, and that will be fun and exciting.  Briana and I are going to Walmart later on to get the supplies!!  I also have to work on a story for political reporting which isn't TOO exciting, but I like to write.  I called KATV earlier and asked about their internships for the spring semester and they're sending me an application.  She said that they usually take however many apply so it shouldn't be that big of a deal since I am going to be a senior next semester.  I REALLY hope that pulls through.  Even if it doesnt I'm quitting my limited job and either becoming a bum or getting a job here.  I think I have a chance at the internship though.  Anyway..  I guess I should get started on school stuff.  BYE

Hello and Happy Election Day!!  I hope that everyone who feels that they should vote has voted, and I would also like to say that I respect those who didn't vote as well and hope that they remained safe today from the insane political crazies who tried to attack them.  Well tonight looks like its going to be a loooong night.  I have to go to the courthouse to watch the election returns as press and do a story about them.  The AR stuff should be done around 9:30 or 10, but I'm sure the presidential election will last well into the night.  I'm probably going to rest up for a few hours now, because I know it will be long, and it will definitely be boring.  Blah.. thats more than enough politics.  Ok well the rest of the day was good, went to Stobys.. weird things happened.  Two guys said that they just got in from Canada yesterday and were headed from Stobys to Baltimore.. We were thinking that they might have been intoxicated.  Well other than that nothing besides politics is going on.  Still loving Justin.. ;)  Almost halfway to the weekend! :)  lol I am pitiful.  Well good luck watching the election tonight!  BYEBYE!

If she seems cold and bitter
Then I beg of you
Just stop and consider
All she's gone through
Don't be quick to condemn her
For things she might say
Just remember
Life turned her that way

She's been walked on
And stepped on
So many times
And I hate to admit it
But the last footprint's mine
She was cryin when I met her
She cries harder today
So don't blame her
Life turned her that way

whoa.. im in a mood

it's amazing how you can speak right to my heart
without saying a word, you can light up the dark :)

actually you said just a couple words, but u made my day more than you have in a long time!  You amaze me.  No matter how down I get about anything, and no matter how much I think you won't be able to turn it around, you do.  And that amazes me.  Just a few little words gave me the most comfort ever and took every doubt and worry I had away.  Once again you amaze me.  You're a wonderful man, and I'm so glad that I took my chances, despite the odds.  You are my rock and always will be.  Even apart, I know you're there for me, and I know that you love me the same.  I love you and I will forever.  

Two roads diverged in a wood, and I -
I took the one less traveled by,  
And that has made all the difference. 


(lol and hello to everyone else)

Hi!  I have not updated in a while, so I thought I would.  Today has been a hectic day.  After 3 classes this morning, I had to go and work on an audio project that I have no clue as to how to do.  I have to make a radio commercial, but our teacher hasn't really explained how to use the equipment.  Anyways after that I came home to prepare for my tv debut.  I did the health segment for the news.  It went pretty well, I think.  My throat's been hurting the past few days and I was scared I would lose my voice.. anyways tonight at 7 I have to go and work on my project some more.  ummm I think that's pretty much my day! byebye!

Better than I was, more than I am 
And all of this happened by taking your hand 
And who I am now is who I wanted to be 
And now that we're together 
I'm stronger than ever 
I'm happy and free 

Oh it's a beautiful thing, don't think I can keep it all in 
If you asked me why I've changed, all I gotta do is say your sweet name

it just does something to me 
it sends a shock right through me 
I can't get enough 
and if you wonder 
about the spell I'm under,

Trying to find their way

And faith that can move anything
They've heard it's all uphill

The world says they'll never make it, love says they will

Hi!  It has been a while since I have updated, but it seems to be working alright today so I will try.  Today was a pretty good day.  I went to just one class, and that was alright.  After that I went to the studio to help one of my tv production classmates on her show.  She's doing a dating game type show and we made the audition tape of some of the girls and guys that showed up to be on it.  I think that next Wed, we actually start the production of her show.  It should be pretty entertaining.  I worked a lot on my own show tonight.  I kinda did the script, and I did the story board and set design.. umm yeah that is boring stuff.  I also wrote a story for political reporting.  I was supposed to make some progress on my audio project.  The written version is due on Friday.  I have to make a commercial for a made-up project.  I didn't really get anything done on it today though.  Ummm tomorrow I have to work from 6-C, not too bad.  The next day I think that JUSTIN is coming over!!!  It's our 4 month anniversary and I think we'll get to hang out for a bit before he does his homework.  That'll be cool.  It's been since Saturday and I miss him and love him lots.  Umm well I think I am going to watch some TV because I have nothing more to say.  Byebye.

Today was quite a long day for me, and I'm very glad to finally be home.  I had to go to class from 9 - 2:40 and that wasn't too bad I suppose, except my last 2 classes are so boring that I just want to explode.  However in spanish I got back my rough draft of my composition and I got an A-, and I was quite pleased with that.  I figured he would grade pretty hard, so I think that is good.  Ummm, I was involved in a racial debate in political reporting that just started from me voicing an opinion, but I do that all the time in there.  That is what she wants though and she said she gives bonus pts for it.  Anyways after class I had to go to a news meeting at 3, we were "supposed" to practice, but by 4:15, I hadn't read yet, so he just let us go.  SO pretty much I sat on a couch in the studio and did nothing for an hour, but I got credit.  After that I had to work 6 to close, and that wasn't too bad.  Pretty short hours.  Ummmmmm tomorrow will be long as well, I have to work from 4 to close.  But this was pretty boring and I had a long day.  But the weekend is just around the corner!!! :)
I am going to see Justin tonight!! YAY!

Today has been a boring day.  I have been doing schoolwork since about 11:00.  I feel "accomplished", however, so that is good.  Justin is very busy today too and I miss him.  I hope that he finishes his studying so that he can talk to me this evening.  I'm very glad that I didn't have to go to school today.  (BTW, Briana can sing Brad Paisley songs VERY VERY WELL!!)  Anyways, I still have more schoolwork to do, but at least I finished all the stuff that I had to do for tomorrow... umm.. anyways I guess it's gonna be just an evening of homework.  So I'm gonna watch TV for a bit first.. and maybe eat some food..

Hi!!!  I just woke up and I am in the best mood ever!!  I got to sleep in, and now I'm watching TV and eating donuts.  Saturdays are the best.  It's kind of stinky that I have to work, but working means money, and also I am going to make a purchase tonight because of this special discount employees are getting on suits this week. But I don't go in until 4 so I get to hang out with Briana until then!!  YAY!  And also after work I am going to NLR, and I get to hang out with Justin!  We will have plenty of time to worry about our homework on Sun and Mon, so we won't have any worries, we just get to relax!  Anyways I think I am going to get back to my "busy" morning.  Have a great Saturday!!

It is the weekend yay!!  And a long one at that.  The extra Monday off is going to do me good because I have an ASSLOAD of homework for the weekend (and that is a lot).  I'll probably start on a bit of it tonight.  I think that me and Briana are going to just chill here for the afternoon then her and Zach are gonna go do somethin.  I'll probably work on some stories or something then.  I might go and visit Marissa and Chelsea's room b/c they wanted me to see what it looked like.  I don't get to to see Justin till tomorrow because he is going dove hunting with his dad today and tomorrow.  But after I get off work tomorrow night I'm going over there and staying the night.  I probably won't stay long Sunday but at least I'll get to see him a little more than I did the other night.  I love him lots and am thankful for the times I do get to see him, even if they are few and far between.  Anyways I am going to watch a bit of TV till Briana gets home.  Have a nice weekend!!

Yay it is Wednesday!  That means that the school week is halfway over, but that also means I have to work tomorrow.  Oh well, it shouldn't be too bad, and i need the $$$.  I also have to work on Saturday, but I have no idea what I'm doing on Friday.  Probably just hanging around here, I suppose.  Justin has to go hunting Friday night/Saturday so I won't see him.  I *might* stay with him Sat after work, but I have no idea if I work Sunday or not.  I really hope I get to see him this weekend at least once, b/c if I don't that shall be sad.  Anyways I am just sitting here watching cartoons, b/c I choose to watch that out of the limited selection of morning programming.  Today is going to be SUCH a long day.  I have TV 2 today, so my classes last from 9 - 2:40, and after my 10, the day gets deathly boring.  I don't know how I stay awake in my 11, audio production, and I feel that TV2 will be just as bad.  Plus I get a PD in BOTH of those classes.  How thrilling for me, huh?  Anyways I guess I will go and try to get on a caffeine high so that I can attempt to be awake today.  I shall update at another time.  Bye Cheeto!!

Hi!  Umm I just wanted to update so that I can go in Briana's room and play the sims.  I really enjoy that game and I think that we are addicted to it.  Anyways I had an alright weekend.  Weird things happened but I am still happy.  And I am SO glad that I got to spend time with Justin, even though it wasn't for very long.  Even though it is Monday, I can't wait till Friday comes again.  Ummm... school was boring today.  I have to go to a news meeting at 3 and then this dumbass campaign kickoff for a dude I don't even know at 7.  I have to go for my political reporting class and then write a story about it.  Woo.  Hoo.  Anyways time for the Sims!!  Comment me!!

Yay!!! I am sooo glad that today is finally Friday.  This week has seemed to take forever!  Being apart from Justin has been hard, but I'm sooo glad that I get to see him tonight.  He is gonna come over tonight, but leave real early in the morning because he gets double the homework on the weekends and that is what he is gonna do on Saturday and Sunday.  Briana has to work ALL day today and that is kinda stinky, but she doesn't go in until 5 tomorrow so we will HAVE to do something fun tomorrow afternoon.  Anyways I am just in a really happy mood and am going to go and learn some Spanish now!!

Good Morning all!  I just woke up, and I am in a very good mood for some reason.  I guess it probably has to do with it just being 9:15 and I just woke up.  I don't have class until 12:15, so I COULD go back to sleep for a while, but I have a quiz in today's class that I must study for a bit.  Despite my good mood, I am NOT looking forward to working.  I haven't worked since last Friday, so I got kinda used to not going.  However, it will give me something to do instead of sit around.  Hopefully it will be busy and the shift will go by fast, and then I will go home and go to sleep and it will be FRIDAY!  YAY!  But anyways, I believe I am going to go and get ready for the day and then study!  Have a nice day everyone!

Well, today is the 3rd day of school and I am NOT excited.  Once again I get to ignore a certain PD.  But I will live.  I just hate going three straight hours in a row.  I'm going to eat lunch in the Student Center again today.. just like in olden times.  I also have to return a book to the book store - DONT LET ME FORGET..  anyways I also get to get started on the news.  I think my first show will be one week from TODAY.  That kinda makes me nervous.  My segment is 5 minutes and that is actually a very long time to talk to a camera.  Anyways after school today I am going to North Little Rock to visit Justin on his last day of freedom.  It makes me sad to know that I'll only see him like one day a week, but I'll survive.  I'm sure I'll get used to it, and it will be worth it in the end.  Anyways I think that I will go and get ready for school now.  I hope that you enjoy this post Briana b/c it is JUST FOR YOU!!!!

Hi!!!  It's Tuesday morning and I have decided to update.  Yesterday was SUCH a productive day.  My TV1 group and I spent five hours shooting for a music video that we have to make.  The footage is GREAT!!  I think we're gonna make an awesome video.  I am in a pretty good mood this morning.  One of my sources for advanced reporting FINALLY emailed me back, so I get to write a story this afternoon that was due last Friday.  Oh well, at least I'm writing it.  I HAVE to laundry today.  It is seriously building up!  I also have to go to city hall tonight at 6 to find a story to write, then go back to stanley russ and write it - it's due by midnight.  That doesn't sound very fun, but it is causing me to miss Media Law - yay!  In other news - I went to CCM State Convention this weekend.  It was SO much fun.  I got a LOT closer to the people in my group and made lots of other new friends.  The dance was my favorite part - there was a lot of latino music and latino guys :)  Anyways I gotsta go and fix my hurr right now!!  Have a great day :)

Hello!  I thought it was time to update, so I thought I would do it.  Today has been a good day.  *:)*  I have a mattress pad.  I had a good class this morning and people were real nice and interested in me.  yay.  Wow.. someone is singing outside.. it's beautiful.  Umm... I was sad last night and I will probably be sad later tonight.  But for right now it's coo.  I don't have class again until 5:30 - yippee!  We'll probably go over to Jennifer's house tonight to celebrate her birthday.  We bought her a cookie cake and it will be yummy.  I still haven't wrapped her gift or anything, but I've got until about 7 so its cool.  Anyways, I believe I'm going to fix me a sandwich and its gon' be good!  HOLLA!  ;)

Hey!  I'm just sitting in my advanced reporting class, waiting on my teacher to arrive! :)  It's already 8:59 - where she is?  Anyways, I am REAL thirsty, and I have no moneys to purchase a beverage! :(  Guess I'll get one when I return to the room.  Today is Friday already!  The week went by awfully fast.  Today is going to be a pretty good day, I reckon.  I have high spirits, and I'm not thinking to much about the "situation."  So, I'll live.  I don't know how excited I am about going to work tonight, however.  I have to work from 5-c, so that means working straight through, no breaks for jessimoo.  Um, I hope we are to learn something interesting today, b/c I'm pretty sweepy.  Someone was talking to me through the wee hours last night! :)  Anyways, what else.. what else.  I've been talking to Abby a lot lately.  She doing good.  Whuh oh - teach is here!  Gotta jet! :)  Have a nice day! :)

Hello!  I haven't updated in a while, and I'm not really doing anything at the moment except for staring at the computer so I thought I would.  Today I was SUPPOSED to have advanced reporting at 9:00, so I walked all the way over there in the freezing cold, and sat down at my regular computer.  At about 5 till, Mrs Debbie (the office lady in my department) came in and told me that I didn't have class today!!  So I was full of mixed emotions - glad that I didn't have class, but really upset b/c I had to make the cold walk right back home!!  Yesterday was a fun day.  We went to LR for a job interview for Briana, and whilst she was interviewing, I took it upon myself to go and shop till I dropped.  I only bought a little bit for me, the majority of my purchases were b-day gifts for kyle and jennifer.  She pulled me out of Victoria's Secret just in time, however.  :)  Well, speaking of the devil the situation w/ kyle is real weird.  I had a long talk w/ abby about it last night seeing as how she seems to be in the situation I will probably be in in about 5 months, and she told me that she STILL misses him after that long.  But, last night we hung out, and it was pretty fun actually.  I just wanted to spill my guts and beg him to take me back - but I didn't.  I wish I just hated him so that I didn't wanna be friends w/ him, but I don't hate him, by golly I love him.  But I'm sure I will forever no matter what happens, b/c it was a first love on both parts.  It just sucks when I think of the fact that he doesn't really love me.  But, anyways I think that we can be friends... I think.  But anyways I have to go and speak spanish to myself in the mirror now b/c I have an oral presentation today after class!!  BYEBYE! :)

Today has turned out to be a sad day.  Kyle and I broke up, and I am sad.  But I'll live.  I'm sad on the inside but decent on the outside.  I am still going home tomorrow, and even though sadness has endured, I'm still REALLY excited about seeing my house and family and kitties and doggie! :)  I'm sure the sadness will go away eventually.

Hey! Today is Thursday which means tomorrow is Friday!! Yippee.. no school and I get to go home.  It's gonna be great.  I get to go shopping on Saturday, maybe Friday with my mom.  And Saturday night I get to hang out with my brother.  That'll be cool.  This morning in TV1 we got to go out and just take some shots in groups.  It was real fun, and I felt quite intelligent, b/c I felt as though I knew what I was doing the whole time and I helped the other group members a lot! :) It was cool.  We get to watch them on Tuesday and see how we did.  Next I get to go to Broadcasting Management! :(  No fun.. that is such a boring class, if you can't already tell by the name.  I haven't even cracked the book.  Well, I think I'm going to watch a lil bit of Full House before class!!  Have a great day!! BYE! :)

Hello!!  It's in between class time so I thought I would update my journal.  This morning I had advanced reporting.  I really love that class, my adviser is my teacher so I already know that she likes me.  She's a real fun lady.  At 11 I have Spanish II, and today we are discussing the chapter that I have been waiting for since I started the program:  LA COMIDA.. FOOD!!  I just love learning that stuff! :)  I learned how to say shrimp:  los camarones!! hehe.. Anypoo today I have to go and film for a package at the volunteer fair.  I was going to be reporter but since my flat iron broker, I cannot achieve the perfect "reporter do" so Betsy is going to do it.  That means I get the harder job, though.  Hopefully I'll be able to white balance a lot better than I did at my last attempt this semester.  Anyways that is at 1:30, then a workshop at 3:00.. then.. nothing!  I don't even think I have any homework tonight!  Life's tough, huh?  I imagine the semester will get much harder, however.  Anyways, my mom is talking to me yahoo so I guess I should end this!!  LEAVE ME A COMMENT!!! :) Bye!

P.S.  IT IS COLD OUTSIDE... BUNDLE UP!!

Hi!! It's been a long time since I've posted, and I have nothing else to do, so I thought I would.  I had a pretty good weekend, I guess.  Just worked everyday.  I'm looking forward to this week b/c I really don't have too much to do and that will be a nice change.  I'm REALLY looking forward to this weekend, b/c after a month of being here I finally am getting a chance to go home.  I'm not really homesick, I just think it'll be real nice to be home for a change.  I'll feel MUCH cleaner! :)  Today is going to be a really fun day!  Briana is going to Park Plaza to apply for a job at some of the stores, which means I will follow behind purchasing many cute items! :)  Cute items that I cannot afford, at that.  It's a disease.  Anyway, I believe that will be great fun.  I get to go to Spanish II in just a little bit and re-write a composition about my daily routine if I lived on a tropical island - exciting, huh?  Well, I think I'm going to watch a bit of TV before I go and learn!!  Hasta pronto! :)  Adios.

Hello!  Today was the first day of school, and it was a VERY long day.  It didn't get started very well, we accidentally overslept!  But, we made it to our first class on time.  It is quite fun being Briana's roommate.  She is being weird right now.. in a funny way   :) "like oh my god you're hot" that is what she said Zach said.. weirdo  hehe.  Anyways tomorrow I have to go to two more new classes yay.  Well it is beddy time.  Night night.

Hello again.  It is time for school again.. yay.  Briana is my roomie, and I think that that will be very fun and exciting.  We have to get up early tomorrow and go learn, which is not my most favoritest thing, but I'm sure I'll get excited about it next week.  My first class is at 9:25, so that's not too bad.  Well... only Briana reads this so HI WEEBS!!!

Hey!  I hope everyone had a great new year!  I had a blast last night.  Me and a bunch of peeps just hung out at my house and were silly.  I think everyone had a lot of fun, and I was so glad that Briana actually came.  I think she had a good time ;)  Umm today I'm not doing anything.  Just eating some food and hanging out with my family.  I know Briana had mentioned something about spending some time w/ me today, so I was going to see if she had wanted to come over.  I called her a few minutes ago but she quickly and mysteriously had to go....  Anywho, maybe we can get together later.  Well, I have to go back to Conway on Saturday, that's two days.  I kind of want to go back, but I kind of don't.  It's kind of sad, but this will probably be the last time I'll ever spend 2 weeks in a row in Hope, because it will no longer be my residence after this summer.  But, anyways, y'all have a great day!  BYE!

Gooood Morning!  I just got home from the dentist and I have NO cavities!  Yay for me.  I had a good weekend.  Did lots of shopping in Memphis and lots of hanging out with the family.  Last night was real fun.  Briana and me and Kyle went to Juan Amigo (hehe) and it was yum.  Briana is sick (sad) but she is going to be my roomie in one week (happy).  I get to go back to work on Saturday, oh joy, and start school next Thursday, double joy.  News Years Eve is umm tomorrow wow.. I have to make some kinda plans today.  I'm sure I'll just invite lots of peeps over to watch movies and shoot fireworks and eat and stuff and that should be plenty fun.  Briana is OLD!  Weird, I will be a teenager and she will be an old hag.. i mean nice lady :)  Well today I really don't know what I'm going to do.  I am up and ready this early, so I'll probably have a long day of nothing.  I need to go and exchange a present and the mall so I might be doing that today, who knows.  Anyways, everyone have a wonderful super day and I will write again soon.

Hello and Merry Late Christmas everyone!  I hope everyone had a wonderful holiday, I know I did.  I've had a GREAT time getting back together with all of my friends and family now that I am back home for a little bit.  I got all sorts of awesome clothes and stuff for Christmas and I had a great time giving presents to everyone else.  I've done quite a lot of stuff since I last updated, but I don't think anything too exciting to describe.  I can't find Briana Wagley!  Where you is?  I would like to eat some pizza with you this evening but you are no where to be found.  Anyways, I'm going to Mema's house tomorrow.  I'm pretty excited, I haven't been there in a while.  She got a computer and the internet for Christmas so I'll be reachable at that time.  I'll be back in Hope on Monday for fun and games with all of my friends.  Anyways, I'll try to remember to update this weekend.  Bye bye and HAPPY KWANZAA!!  - aww briana cannot play i am sad

Hey guys!!  How's it going?  We got the internet yesterday!  WOOP.  But, I've been so busy this week this is the first chance I have gotten to actually use it, and I can't really be on it very long b/c I have to go set up some Christmas things in a minute.  Well, anywho, my week was really good.  I worked all day Thursday, Friday, and today.  On Friday, Jennifer and I went to the movies and saw Mona Lisa Smile.  It was really, really good.  I suggest it.  This Wednesday, Kyle came and visited!! :)  We had a good time, except for we got lost in North Little Rock trying to find his mom, but we found our way back.  I'm going back to Hope tomorrow morning (yippee), and will be staying there until January 3, I think.  And, Cynthia Briana Wagley, when are you going to be registering for your classes?  I have been wanting to call you and ask you about it for the past two days but by the time I pick up the phone it's like 1:30 am or something and I don't want to wake you.  Perhaps I will call you this evening :)  Anyways, this is my life in the past week.  Well, a really really condensed version.  I'm sure you'll hear all about it when I get home.  Well, I guess bye for now! :)

Hello again.  I just felt as though I should update before I left to go back to the internet-less apartment of doom.  Well, it's not necessarily an apartment of "doom."  I just really don't want to go back.  I don't want to leave my mommy or Brianie :(  I will leave Kyle because he is mean, but oh well.  Did you like my comment in which I left you, Briana?  (itchy itchy wee wee)  I thought it was very funny.  Anyways, I ate at Cherry's today.  It was quite delicioso, and I get to go back home and sit and stare at the tv for the rest of the day.  I need to save mi minutos, BUT i'll probably end up giving in and calling Briana out of boredom.  Well, hopefully we'll get the internet sometime this week and I will post again then, but if not it will be Monday the 22nd the next time you hear from me.  BYE! :)

Hello!  I am finally back online for a couple of days.  Living at Jennifer's apartment is really fun, but the no internet thing kind of sucks.  I think we're getting it hooked up sometime this week, though, so that is cool.  I'm SOOO glad my finals are over!!  I was in a wonderful mood all weekend, even when I had to work ALL day EVERY day, just b/c of no more school, especially no more gaughan's world lit! :)  Well today I am going to go over to my cousin's house to play for a little while.  Then, tonight I'm hanging w/ Briana and we are going to eat at Little B's YUM!  I'm excited!  I like spending time w/ her, and she better be living with me in Conway next year or I will be :(.  Anywho, I've gotta leave now.  Byebye!

Hello gang!  Right now I am studying for my big American Nations test.  I'm not really retaining much information at the moment, so I thought I would write a bit in the journal.  I also wanted to say that I will be internet-less for quite sometime, because I am moving in with Jennifer for a little bit over Christmas break, and she hasn't gotten the internet hooked up at her place yet.
